==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Megascopical
<hw>Meg`a*scop"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the megascope or the projection upon a screen
of images of opaque objects.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Enlarged or
magnified; -- said of images or of photographic pictures, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Large enough to be seen; -- said
of the larger structural features and components of rocks which do not
require the use of the microscope to be perceived. Opposed to
<ant>microscopic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Megaseme</ent>⟦br⟧
